      "All user-visible strings go through t('key'). Hard-coded English is a bug.",
      "Spanish takes ~30% more horizontal space — design for that.",
      "Title Case in English ↔ Title Case in Spanish for buttons/headers; sentence case ↔ sentence case for body.",
      "Church terms in Spanish follow the official handbook: barrio, estaca, obispado, llamamiento, sostener, apartar, relevar, Sumo Sacerdote, Élder, Sacerdocio de Melquisedec, Alto Consejo (CH), Presidencia de Estaca (PE).",
      "Numbers/dates use Intl.NumberFormat / Intl.DateTimeFormat with the active locale — never concatenate."
    ]
